1. Download any Python 3
 https://www.python.org/downloads/

2. Follow the installation Wizard windows 

3. To check whether Python is installed or not type the following command in CMD
	python --version

4. Before checking the version  add the Python installation floder path in the  variables.


--------------------------

1. Install the Git for windows (source code management)
2.https://git-scm.com/download/win 
3.Install the downloaded .exe file
4. After installation , just type the 
	git -version

5. And In every floder , you  can able to see two option (GIT BASH , GITG GUI)


---------------------------------
MINI Conda (Jupyter Notebook)

1. Install the mini conda 
2. https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/latest/user-guide/install/windows.html
3. Once it is installed , you can able to see the Anaconda Prompt (just like a cmd)
4. Anacoda prompt is used to launch the jupyter notebook.


--------------------------------

Pull the Repo.

1. Go the required Path

2. Open the Git bash
	git clone <url>
3. git clone https://github.com/anil-k-rajamoni18/Python_Session_June.git

4. Every time to get the lastest changes , just do 
	git pull
	by going to the ORIGINAL REPO FLODER (where you have cloned)

5. NOTE : Please don't make any changes in the ORIGINAL REPO FLODER . Because you won't get the changes
	

--------------------------------
	JUPYTER NOTEBOOK
1. Go to the your path
2. Open Anaconda Prompt 
3. Change the path using (cd <path>)
4. to open jupyter notebook type : jupyter notebook
5. It will be opened in the default browser.



